</span><br /><span id="victor_an357" class="victor_header">Document Type: Journal articles (080); Reports--Research (143)</span></p>
<p><span id="victor_an358" class="victor_paragraph">Examines the relationship between grade configuration in rural schools and student attendance, suspension, and academic achievement for grades 6, 7, 10, and 11. In a large random sample of rural Louisiana schools, students in elementary schools (K-
</span><br /><span id="victor_an359" class="victor_continuation">6/7) and unit schools (K-12) outperformed their middle and secondary school peers. Contains 25 references. (Author/CDS)</span></p>
